THOUGHT: The patch did not resolve the issue, as the same error persists. The problem seems to be related to the dominance of instructions and their uses, as indicated by the error "Instruction does not dominate all uses!" I need to ensure that all instructions dominate their uses after loop unrolling. I will modify the `simplifyLoopAfterUnroll` function to include a dominance check and fix any violations.

```bash
sed -i '/simplifyLoopIVs(L, SE, DT, LI, TTI, DeadInsts);/a \
    for (BasicBlock *BB : L->getBlocks()) { \
        for (Instruction &I : *BB) { \
            for (Use &U : I.operands()) { \
                if (Instruction *Op = dyn_cast<Instruction>(U)) { \
                    if (!DT->dominates(Op, &I)) { \
                        Op->moveBefore(&I); \
                    } \
                } \
            } \
        } \
    }' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/LoopUnroll.cpp
```

